.TH "intel_pmc_gcr_update" 9 "intel_pmc_gcr_update" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
intel_pmc_gcr_update \- Update PMC GCR register bits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" intel_pmc_gcr_update
.BI "(struct intel_pmc_dev *pmc "  ","
.BI "u32 offset "  ","
.BI "u32 mask "  ","
.BI "u32 val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pmc" 12
PMC device pointer
.IP "offset" 12
offset of GCR register from GCR address base
.IP "mask" 12
bit mask for update operation
.IP "val" 12
update value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Updates the bits of given GCR register as specified by
\fImask\fP and \fIval\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
Negative value on error or 0 on success.
